narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Turkish L2 is basically the same as L1, with even more grammar.

This is a continuing language class and it's not very different from Turkish 110. Same teacher, same textbook, same routine. I certainly liked it. The language gets more interesting, too, especially when you get into adverbial constructions of time, like -(y)ken and -(y)ncE. Make sure you take the class seriously (it's easy not to) and ask Etem questions about Turkish culture and history (especially Ottoman stuff).
A fun language class, and an interesting language. Professor Erol is great. Definitely take it.
